<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="152" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="152">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="152">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilothauma hibaratertium" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">Nilothauma hibaratertium</taxonomicName>
has never been described sufficiently, especially in the coloration of the adult. Examination of fresh specimens showed that the foreleg of the adult has distinct dark markings on the base and sub-apex of femora, and the apices of tibia and tarsomere 1. This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nilothauma hibaratertium" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">Nilothauma hibaratertium</taxonomicName>
from the Oriental region; previously, this species has only been recorded from Palaearctic Japan (
<bibRefCitation author="Yamamoto, M" journalOrPublisher="The Entomological Society of Japan" pageId="11" pageNumber="154" pagination="237 - 362" title="Catalogue of the Insects of Japan. Vol. 8, Part 1 Diptera (Nematocera - BrachyceraAschiza)" year="2014">Yamamoto and Yamamoto 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
